comment: The convolution square of this sequence is A007248, except for the constant term: T8D(q)^2 = T4C(q^2) - 8. - _G. A. Edgar_, Apr 02 2017

formula: Expansion of q^(1/2)*(eta(q) / eta(q^4))^4 in powers of q. - _G. A. Edgar_, Apr 02 2017
a(0) = 1, a(n) = -(4/n)*Sum_{k=1..n} A046897(k)*a(n-k) for n > 0. - _Seiichi Manyama_, Apr 28 2017
mathematica: eta[q_]:= q^(1/24)*QPochhammer[q]; a:= CoefficientList[Series[q^(1/2)*(eta[q]/eta[q^4])^4, {q, 0, 50}], q]; Table[a[[n]], {n, 1, 50}] (* _G. C. Greubel_, May 10 2018 *)
